500|$|Per the {{conditions}} of its agreement with the groups, the company filed a petition in 2002 with the Food and Drug Administration requesting the United States Department of Agriculture (USDA) step up enforcement of the <b>Humane</b> <b>Slaughter</b> Act of 1958. The USDA agreed with the request, stating [...] "it is granting your petition and is developing a proposed rule that addresses the issue of humane handling." [...] The USDA failed to indicate when it intended to publish the proposal in the Federal Register and solicit public comment, {{which would be the}} first step before the agency drafts a final rule.|$|E
